<div class="row">
  <div class="column side">
    <h2>Best Conditions</h2>
    <p>If you live in warmer climates, you can direct sow seeds outdoors, but wait until the soil temperature warms to at least 65 degrees.</p>
    <p>If you are in a cooler zone, start seeds indoors about a month before transplanting. Cantaloupe vines are very tender and should not be transplanted until all danger of frost has passed.</p>
    </div>
  <div class="column middle">
    <h2>How to Grow</h2>
    <p> Plant seeds one inch deep, 18 inches apart, in hills about 3 feet apart. If you have limited space, vines can be trained to a support. </p>
    <img src="https://goo.gl/T4Toda" width="180" height="150">

